11:04.568 --> 11:06.851
did they have when you were growing up there? We had 
pikes. They called them pikes. And they were made

11:10.817 --> 11:13.241
out of pine gravel. Well, was a pike like what we 
call a highway? Yeah, uh-huh. And when it rained,

11:19.731 --> 11:23.717
all that stuff just packed together. You see, it 
didn't get muddy. And that's the kind of sidewalks

11:26.441 --> 11:30.947
people had. Where I was born and reared, I was born 
and married out of the house that I was born in. My

11:39.450 --> 11:46.178
daddy had all around the house, and he had three or 
four barns, and that kind of walkways to the barns.

11:46.879 --> 11:53.467
It was nothing in the world but more of a fine 
dust-like.

11:54.288 --> 11:56.771
And you wet that, and you cemented together. It 
